text: Thryptomene globifera is a shrub species in the family Myrtaceae that is endemic to Western Australia. The shrub is found in the Mid West region of Western Australia between Northampton and the Chapman Valley near Geraldton where it grows in sandy soils. ==References== globifera Category:Endemic flora of Western Australia Category:Rosids of Western Australia Category:Plants described in 2014 Category:Taxa named by Barbara Lynette Rye
title: Thryptomene globifera
